AdminChanged(address,address).details: Emitted when the admin account has changed.

BeaconUpgraded(address).details: Emitted when the beacon is changed.

Initialized(uint8).details: Triggered when the contract has been initialized or reinitialized.

Paused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is triggered by `account`.

Unpaused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is lifted by `account`.

Upgraded(address).details: Emitted when the implementation is upgraded.

deposit(address,uint256,uint256,uint256,.details: Deposits tokens in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {lpPair} and deposits tokens in it. Emits a {Deposit} event.

params.amountAMin: - Bounds the extent to which the B/A price can go up before the transaction reverts.
params.amountBMin: - Bounds the extent to which the A/B price can go up before the transaction reverts.
params.lpPair: - Address of the pool to deposit tokens in.
params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.

returns.liquidity: - Total liquidity sent to the farm (in lpTokens).
returns.sentA: - Token A amount sent to the farm.
returns.sentB: - Token B amount sent to the farm.

depositETH(address,uint256,uint256,uint2.details: Autoconverts BNB into WBNB and deposits tokens in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {lpStakingPool} and deposits tokens in it. Emits a {Deposit} event.

params.amountETHMin: - Bounds the extent to which the WBNB/TOKEN price can go up before the transaction reverts.
params.amountTokenMin: - Bounds the extent to which the TOKEN/WBNB price can go up before the transaction reverts.
params.lpPair: - Address of the pool to deposit tokens in.
params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.

returns.liquidity: - Total liquidity sent to the farm (in lpTokens).
returns.sentETH: - WBNB amount sent to the farm.
returns.sentToken: - Token amount sent to the farm.

depositLP(address,uint256,address).details: Deposits tokens in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {lpPair} and deposits tokens in it. Emits a {Deposit} event.

params.lpPair: - Address of the pool to deposit tokens in.
params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.

depositSingleAsset(address,address,uint2.details: Deposits single token in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {lpPair}, swaps {token} for pool tokens and deposits them. Emits a {Deposit} event.

params.amountAMin: - Bounds the extent to which the B/A price can go up before the transaction reverts.
params.amountBMin: - Bounds the extent to which the A/B price can go up before the transaction reverts.
params.lpPair: - Address of the pool to deposit tokens in.
params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.
params.swapData: - Parameter with which 1inch router is being called with.
params.token: - Address of a token to enter the pool.

returns.liquidity: - Total liquidity sent to the farm (in lpTokens).
returns.sent: - Total {token} amount sent to the farm. NOTE: Returns dust left from swap in {token}, but if A/B amounts are not correct also returns dust in pool's tokens.

depositSingleETH(address,bytes[2],uint25.details: Deposits single BNB in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {lpPair}, swaps BNB for pool tokens and deposits them. Emits a {Deposit} event.

params.amountAMin: - Bounds the extent to which the B/A price can go up before the transaction reverts.
params.amountBMin: - Bounds the extent to which the A/B price can go up before the transaction reverts.
params.lpPair: - Address of the pool to deposit tokens in.
params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.
params.swapData: - Parameter with which 1inch router is being called with. NOTE: Use WBNB as toToken.

returns.liquidity: - Total liquidity sent to the farm (in lpTokens).
returns.sentETH: - Total BNB amount sent to the farm. NOTE: Returns dust left from swap in BNB, but if A/B amount are not correct also returns dust in pool's tokens.

params.feeTo: - Address to collect fees to. Note: This function can only be called by the distributor.
params.lpPair: - LP pool to distribute tokens in.
params.swapInfos: - Arrays of structs with token arrays describing swap routes (rewardTokenToTokenA, rewardTokenToTokenB, rewarderTokenToTokenA, rewarderTokenToTokenB) and minimum amounts of output tokens that must be received for the transaction not to revert.

params.lpPair: - LP pair to check tokens in.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

params._fee: -New fee to collect from farms. [10^18 == 100%] Note: This function can only be called by ADMIN_ROLE.

totalDeposits(address).details: Returns total amount locked in the pool. Doesn't take pending rewards into account.

params.lpPair: - LP pool to check total deposits in.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

userStake(address,address).details: Returns tokens staked by the {_address} for the given {lpPair}.

params._address: - The address to check stakes for.
params.lpPair: - LP pool to check stakes in.

withdraw(address,uint256,uint256,uint256.details: Withdraws a pair of tokens from the given pool. Emits a {Withdraw} event.

params.amountAMin: - The minimum amount of tokenA that must be received for the transaction not to revert.
params.amountBMin: - The minimum amount of tokenB that must be received for the transaction not to revert.
params.recipient: - The address which will receive tokens.

returns.amountA: - Token A amount sent to the {recipient}
returns.amountB: - Token B amount sent to the {recipient}

withdrawETH(address,uint256,uint256,uint.details: Autoconverts WBNB into BNB and withdraws tokens from the pool. Emits a {Withdraw} event.

params.amountETHMin: - The minimum amount of BNB that must be received for the transaction not to revert.
params.amountTokenMin: - The minimum amount of token that must be received for the transaction not to revert.
params.recipient: - The address which will receive tokens.

withdrawLP(address,uint256,address).details: Withdraws LP tokens from the given pool. Emits a {Withdraw} event.

params.recipient: - The address which will receive tokens.

withdrawSingleAsset(address,uint256,addr.details: Withdraws single token from the given pool. Emits a {Withdraw} event. Note: If there are any tokens left to be withdrawn after swaps they will be sent to the {{recipient}} in a respective token (not in {token}).

params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.
params.swapData: - Parameter with which 1inch router is being called with.
params.token: - Address of a token to exit the pool with.

returns.amountA: - Token A dust sent to the {recipient}.
returns.amountB: - Token B dust sent to the {recipient}.

withdrawSingleETH(address,uint256,bytes[.details: Withdraws single BNB from the given pool. Emits a {Withdraw} event. Note: If there are any tokens left to be withdrawn after swaps they will be sent to the {{recipient}} in a respective token (not in BNB).

params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.
params.swapData: - Parameter with which 1inch router is being called with.

returns.amountA: - Token A dust sent to the {recipient}.
returns.amountB: - Token B dust sent to the {recipient}.
